{"ts": "2026-06-12T17:32:50.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "Level X task analysis", "agent": "orchestrator-lx", "tokens_in": 1504, "tokens_out": 600, "elapsed_ms": 7967, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level X Orchestrator — the central intelligence of the system.\nYou plan, test, and report. You decide when to delegate to workers.\n\n## Task Analysis\nAnalyze the user's task and output a JSON plan:\n\n{\n  \"plan\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"short-name\",\n      \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\",\n      \"need_worker\": true\n    }\n  ],\n  \"key_requirements\": [\"list the 2-4 critical things that must work\"]\n}\n\n## Rules\n- Prefer ONE worker that handles EVERYTHING end-to-end. Only split if tasks\n  require fundamentally different expertise (e.g., Python backend + React frontend).\n- Most frontend UI tasks need exactly ONE worker: it writes HTML, CSS, and JS itself.\n- task_id must be unique short names like \"ui\", \"api\", \"docs\".\n- Each description must include exact output file names.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text.\n\n## User Request\nBuild the Orcheeos Platform Dashboard — a ChatGPT-style interface for running agent tasks with live log streaming.\n\n## FILES: index.html, styles.css, app.js\n\n## CRITICAL RULES\n- NO mock data. NO fake SSE events. ALL data comes from real fetch() calls to localhost:8000.\n- Chat is the ONLY interface. No extra panels, no health grids, no separate SSE feeds.\n- Full viewport layout: body overflow:hidden. Only sidebar and chat panel scroll internally.\n\n## LAYOUT (ChatGPT clone)\n- Left sidebar (260px): dark, \"New Chat\" button, history list (scrollable). Each item: first 40 chars of task + timestamp. Click to load.\n- Right area (fills rest): top bar with username + \"Logout\", chat messages (scrollable), input area at bottom fixed.\n- NO page-level scrollbar. scroll only inside sidebar and chat panel.\n- Dark theme (#111 or #0f172a — your choice). Clean, professional.\n\n## LOGIN\n- One input: username. \"Enter\" button. Save to localStorage(\"orcheeos_user\").\n- If username exists in localStorage, skip login. Show dashboard directly.\n- No password. No demo text. No mock auth.\n\n## CHAT INTERFACE\n- Input bar at bottom (sticky): text input + Level dropdown + Specialty dropdown + \"Run\" button.\n- Level options: baseline1, baseline2, level1b, levelx, 1, 2, 3\n- Specialty options: frontend, backend, brand, fullstack, research\n- Default: level=levelx, specialty=frontend\n- User message: right-aligned bubble (blue/accent bg)\n- System/log messages: left-aligned bubble (dark gray bg) as they stream in\n- Send with Enter or Ctrl+Enter\n\n## REAL API INTEGRATION (NO MOCKS)\n\nWhen user clicks \"Run\":\n1. POST to http://localhost:8000/api/v1/run\n   Headers: Content-Type: application/json\n   Body: {\"level\": selectedLevel, \"specialty\": selectedSpecialty, \"task\": userInput, \"user\": username}\n\n2. The response is SSE (Server-Sent Events). Read the stream body:\n   - Each line: \"data: \" + JSON\n   - Parse JSON, extract: event, msg, agent, tokens_in, tokens_out, model, task_id\n   - Display each event as a left-aligned bubble with event type badge and message text\n   - Store task_id from the first event that has it\n\n3. ASSIGNMENT: Show a loading state while connecting. On first event, show the log stream.\n\n4. When event.event === \"task_complete\" OR \"run_finished\":\n   - Show \"Preview\" button → opens window.open(\"/api/v1/preview/frontend/\" + username + \"/\" + taskId + \"/main/index.html\")\n   - Show \"Download ZIP\" button → opens window.open(\"/api/v1/artifacts/\" + taskId)\n   - Save this chat to history (localStorage key \"orcheeos_history\")\n\n## HISTORY SIDEBAR\n- localStorage key: \"orcheeos_history\" — JSON array of {task_id, preview (first 50 chars of task), timestamp, level, specialty}\n- Each click loads messages from stored events array into chat panel\n- \"New Chat\" clears panel. \"Clear History\" button at sidebar bottom.\n\n## SSE PARSE CODE (use exactly this)\n```javascript\nasync function runTask(task, level, specialty, username) {\n  const response = await fetch(\"http://localhost:8000/api/v1/run\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    body: JSON.stringify({level, specialty, task, user: username})\n  });\n  const reader = response.body.getReader();\n  const decoder = new TextDecoder();\n  let buffer = \"\", taskId = \"\";\n  while (true) {\n    const {done, value} = await reader.read();\n    if (done) break;\n    buffer += decoder.decode(value, {stream: true});\n    const lines = buffer.split(\"\\n\");\n    buffer = lines.pop() || \"\";\n    for (const line of lines) {\n      if (line.startsWith(\"data: \")) {\n        try {\n          const event = JSON.parse(line.slice(6));\n          if (!taskId && event.task_id) taskId = event.task_id;\n          onLogEvent(event); // your display function\n        } catch(e) {}\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return taskId;\n}\n```\n\n## DISPLAY EACH SSE EVENT\nShow as a compact log line: event type badge (colored small pill) + message text + optional details (model name, token counts for llm_call events)\nColor badges: planner=#60a5fa, worker=#34d399, error=#ef4444, report=#fbbf24, llm_call=#a78bfa, tool_call=#9ca3af, default=#6b7280\n\n## HEALTH CHECK\n- On load: fetch(\"http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health\")\n- If not {\"status\":\"ok\"}, show red banner \"Server Offline\" at top\n- Check every 30s\n\n## STYLING\n- Dark theme. Clean typography. Monospace font for log messages.\n- User bubbles: background accent blue, white text, right-aligned\n- System bubbles: background #1e293b, left-aligned\n- Input area: dark bg, subtle border, good padding\n- Sidebar items: hover highlight, active indicator\n- Smooth transitions", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T17:33:36.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Level X Agent Creator — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-lx", "tokens_in": 765, "tokens_out": 3942, "elapsed_ms": 45763, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level X Agent Creator. Create worker configurations with tool suggestions.\n\n## Available Tools (full menu)\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Recommended Tools (suggest these for every worker)\nwrite_file, read_file, list_files, generate_image, render_html_file_screenshot, read_image, validate_html, validate_css, run_command\n\n## Task Plan\n[\n  {\n    \"task_id\": \"ui\",\n    \"description\": \"Build the complete Orcheeos Platform Dashboard: produce index.html, styles.css, and app.js. Implement ChatGPT-style interface with real SSE streaming from localhost:8000, login with localStorage, history sidebar, health check, and artifact preview/download links. No mock data.\",\n    \"need_worker\": true\n  }\n]\n\n## Rules\n- Create EXACTLY the workers specified in the plan — no extra, no missing\n- Each worker gets the RECOMMENDED tools above PLUS any additional tools from the full menu that are needed\n- Each worker's system_prompt MUST push them toward COMPLETE end-to-end delivery:\n  \"You are responsible for the COMPLETE deliverable. Solve everything end-to-end. Write ALL files. Validate ALL output. If you need an image, use generate_image. If you need to verify, use screenshots. Do NOT leave work for others.\"\n- worker_name MUST match the task_id from the plan\n- system_prompt: detailed role + boundaries + workflow + output format\n- Keep it simple: 1-2 workers is ideal\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"task_id_from_plan\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full custom system instructions pushing toward end-to-end completion\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\", \"...\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Reference Templates (suggestions only - pick what makes sense)\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  }\n]", "meta": {}}
